The purposes of the meeting are to:
 1 Elect the directors of the Company for the ensuing year;
 2 Appoint PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as independent auditor of the Company for the 2026 financial year and authorize the directors to fix their remunerations;
 3 Approve the continuation, amendment, and restatement of the Company's Shareholder Right's plan;
 4 Set the number of directors of the Company at nine;
 5 Receive the audited consolidated financial statements of the Company for the financial year ended December 31, 2025, together with the report of the independent auditor thereon; and
 6 Transact such other business as may properly come before the Meeting or any adjournment or postponement thereof.


 Leigh Curyer,
 President & Chief Executive Officer
